Children.Name: TitlePage

Children.Text: Progression through each of the phenological stages is driven by thermal time.  As temperature increases from zero to 30 degrees, development acelerates and then slows down again above 30 degress
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: As ThermalTime accumulates the crop progresses through the following phases:
Children.Name: Description1

Children.Text: Currently the duration of the Emergence phase is set to zero because the period of zero cover and biomass production following sowing is accounted for in the cover and biomass accumulation functions.  However this phase is included if parameterisations of other crops in the future wish to give this phase a duration.
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: During this phase the plant only partitions biomass to Root and Stover (leaf and stem) Organs
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: During this phase the plant is partitioning biomass to Root, Stover and Product organs.
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: During this phase the plant is partitioning biomass to Root and Product organs and the canopy cover decreases from its maximum to zero
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: During this phase the plant has completed its growth and is drying ready for harvest.
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: It is the biomass that is removed from the crop at harvest and may include grain, root, leaf, stem, pod or any other organ type depending on the type of crop and how it is harvested.
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This is the Product yield (g/m2 fresh weight) that SCRUM will predict provided nitrogen and water supply are non-limiting
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This is the dry matter content of the harvested yield and is used to convert fresh yield into *DryYield* which are subsequently used in determining *Ymax* (total biomass production), daily dry matter production, *HarvestIndex* and the *PartitioningFraction* of each organ
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This variable is the product yield of the crop in g/m2 dry weight
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This is used to convert the total Dry Matter of this organ back to fresh mass once daily partitining is complete.
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This is the Product yield (g/m2 fresh weight) that SCRUM will predict provided nitrogen and water supply are non-limiting
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: Stover represents any part of the crop that is not removed at harvest (i.e not part of the product).
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: The extinction coefficient is used to calculate a LAI value (needed by MicroClimate) from the canopy cover
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: Is a coefficient for the potential biomass accumulation function
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: Is another coefficient for the potential biomass accumulation function
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: This variable is the total biomass (g/m2dry weight) that the crop will produce at maturity in the absence of stress
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: DM demand is based on a simple partitioning coefficients.  At harvest the biomass partitioned to the stover = TotalDM * (1 - RootProportion) * (1 - Harvest index).  However the partitioningFraction is more complicated that this as it partitions more biomass to the stover in the CanopyExpanding Phase and less in the Yield increasing phase to give realistic patterns of accumulation of biomass in the Stover and Product over the duration of the crop
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: The root organ demands and is partitioned N and DM and its depth increases through time to provide a water uptake supply
Children.Name: Description
Description

Children.Text: This is the proportion of total biomass that is paritioned into the roots and is used to set the partitioning fraction for the roots
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: The nodule organ is unparameterised and simply has a switch that is turned on for legume crops (so they can fix what ever N the crop demands) and switched off for non legume crops (which fix no N)
Children.Name: Description

Children.Text: The AboveGround composite biomass object includes Stover and Product organs.
Children.Name: memo
